Second Department,

October, 1966

(October 3, 1966)* In the Matter of Robert M. Stein, Petitioner, v. Appellate Term of the Supreme Court of the State of New York, Second Judicial Department, et al., Respondents.

Not published with other decisions of October 3, 1966, 26 A D 2d 818.— [Rep.

Proceeding pursuant to CPLR article 78 to prohibit and enjoin respondents from proceeding with or entertaining an appeal taken by the respondent District Attorney to the respondent court in People v. Robert M. Stein. Proceeding dismissed, without costs. Beldoek, P. J., Ughetta, Christ, Brennan and Hill, JJ., concur.
